{"id": "eds1665702557855", "title": "Using Sort Options", "breadcrumbs": ["Scripting Application Behavior", "Sorting Data in ProcScript", "Using Sort Options"], "url": "https://docs.rocketsoftware.com/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html", "html": "<html><body><header class=\"zDocsTopicPageHead\"><h1 class=\"css-g931ng\">Using Sort Options</h1><div class=\"zDocsTopicActions\" role=\"list\"><div class=\"zDocsBundlePagination\" data-testid=\"next-prev-container\" role=\"listitem\"><div class=\"zDocsPrevTopicButton zDocsPrevTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Previous:   Sorting Data in ProcScript \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Previous:   Sorting Data in ProcScript \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vkk1665702553651.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-prev\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-prev\"></use></svg></a></span></div><div class=\"zDocsNextTopicButton zDocsNextTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Next:   Sorting Lists and Sublists \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Next:   Sorting Lists and Sublists \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwg1665702557778.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></a></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsMyDocsMenu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Add to My Topics\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Add to My Topics\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" id=\"addToMyDocsDropdownTrigger\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/eds1665702557855.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527089\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527089\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104eds1665702557855.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eds1665702557855.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eds1665702557855.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"eds1665702557855\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Using Sort Options\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The following examples demonstrate how you can use the sort options to control sorting behavior.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16811e1_d16812e1_d16813e1\">The specific examples use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sort</span> statement, but the sort options can also be used with lists. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qwg1665702557778.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qwg1665702557778.html\" title=\"The ProcScript commands sort/list, $sortlist, and $sortlistid enable you to sort all kinds of lists, including indexed lists (flat lists), associative lists (such as property lists and ValRep lists), and nested lists (such as those used in tree widgets).\">Sorting Lists and Sublists</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eds1665702557855__section_krx_gkx_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d259011e73\">Example: Sort Order</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16817e1_d16818e1_d16819e1\">You can explicitly set the search order by specifying\n            the <span class=\"keyword option\">ascending</span> or <span class=\"keyword option\">descending</span> search option (or their\n            abbreviations). For example, given a set of occurrences of entity TEL_CODES:</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eds1665702557855__fig_d16820e1_d16821e1_d16822e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Unsorted List of Countries</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Grid with columnsCountry and International Code, unsorted\" class=\"image\" id=\"eds1665702557855__image_nzh_3kx_tcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sortcountrytelcodes_header.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16826e1_d16827e1_d16828e1\">Use the following command to sort in descending order\n            by country:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"eds1665702557855__pre_ozh_3kx_tcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">sort/e TELCODES, COUNTRY: descending</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eds1665702557855__fig_d16829e1_d16830e1_d16831e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 2. </span>Countries Sorted in Descending Order</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Grid with columns Country and International Code, sorted by Country in descending order\" class=\"image\" id=\"eds1665702557855__image_pzh_3kx_tcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sortcountrytelcodes_entitysorted_d.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16835e1_d16836e1_d16837e1\">By default, Uniface sorts data using a binary sort\n            order. However, if the locale is specified, it can apply locale-based rules for sorting\n            data using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$nlssortorder</span>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jvl1665702552585.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jvl1665702552585.html\" title=\"You can sort data in ProcScript using several ProcScript statements and functions. The default sort order is determined by the data type of the data and the values of NLS settings.\">Sorting Based on Locale</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eds1665702557855__section_jdk_dkx_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d259011e128\">Example: Removing Items with Duplicate Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16838e1_d16839e1_d16840e1\">It is possible to remove duplicate items from a list\n            using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">unique</code> sort option. For example, an entity TELCODES has\n            fields representing the international calling codes for countries (ICODE and COUNTRY).\n            Both Canada and the United States have the international calling code of\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>:</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eds1665702557855__fig_d16841e1_d16842e1_d16843e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 3. </span>Duplicate Field Values</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Grid with columns Country and International Code, showing Canada and the United States with the same international code (1)\" class=\"image\" id=\"eds1665702557855__image_jpj_2kx_tcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sortcountrytelcodes_entitysorted_u1.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16847e1_d16848e1_d16849e1\">The following ProcScript instruction sorts the list by\n            calling code and removes occurrences with a duplicate value:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"eds1665702557855__pre_kpj_2kx_tcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">sort \"TELCODES.TEL\", \"ICODE: u\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16850e1_d16851e1_d16852e1\">Only the first occurrence of the duplicate value is\n            included in the result.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eds1665702557855__fig_d16853e1_d16854e1_d16855e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 4. </span>Unique Field Values</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Grid with columns Country and International Code, showing only Canada and not the United States\" class=\"image\" id=\"eds1665702557855__image_lpj_2kx_tcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sortcountrytelcodes_entitysorted_u.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eds1665702557855__section_p55_wjx_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d259011e174\">Example: Sorting Using Data Type</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16859e1_d16860e1_d16861e1\">When sorting occurrences, Uniface uses the data type\n            of the specified sort field. Thus, a numeric field is sorted in numerical order, a Date\n            field is sorted according to its internal data format, and will therefore sort\n            correctly. ( For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lqt1665702557960.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lqt1665702557960.html\" title=\"The internal format is a standard format based on the data type of the data concerned, usually combined with the packing code definition. No additional external formatting (such as a display format) is applied. Uniface handles all data in components in the internal format.\">Internal Data Format</a>.) If you\n            specify a data type or data type format, for example <span class=\"keyword option\">Numeric</span> or\n               <span class=\"keyword option\">$number</span>, it overrides the field's default data type.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16862e1_d16863e1_d16864e1\">When sorting lists, all data is treated as string data\n            by default.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16865e1_d16866e1_d16867e1\">Specifying another data type is particularly useful\n            when the <var class=\"keyword varname\">ElementToSortBy</var> has data type String but contains numbers,\n            because the sort is by character, which results in 100 sorting before 19. For example,\n            the TELCODES entity has its field PK defined as a string. The following ProcScript\n            instruction sorts occurrences by the PK field:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"eds1665702557855__pre_izs_xjx_tcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">sort/e \"TELCODE\", \"PK: a\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16868e1_d16869e1_d16870e1\">This results in <code class=\"ph codeph\">PK=11</code> sorting before\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">PK=2</code>.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eds1665702557855__fig_d16871e1_d16872e1_d16873e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 5. </span>String Field With Numbers Sorted as String</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Grid with columns PK, Country, and International Code, sorted by PK as a string (1, 11, 2, 25, etc.)\" class=\"image\" id=\"eds1665702557855__image_kzs_xjx_tcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sortcountrytelcodes_pk.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16877e1_d16878e1_d16879e1\">To sort the field as a numeric data type, use the\n            following ProcScript instruction:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"eds1665702557855__pre_lzs_xjx_tcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">sort/e \"TELCODE\", \"PK: a numeric\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eds1665702557855__fig_d16880e1_d16881e1_d16882e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 6. </span>String Field With Numbers Sorted as Numeric</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Grid with columns PK, Country, and International Code, sorted by PK as a number (1,2,3 etc.)\" class=\"image\" id=\"eds1665702557855__image_nzs_xjx_tcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sortcountrytelcodes_pk2.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eds1665702557855__section_jl3_tjx_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d259011e246\">Example: Sorting by Hierarchical Level </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16886e1_d16887e1_d16888e1\">You can also specify a hierarchical sort if the\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">ElementToSortBy</var> contains numbers that represent a hierarchy, such\n            as <var class=\"keyword varname\">n.n.n</var>, where each period represents another level in the\n            hierarchy. For example, the following list of telephone are codes for Canada has a LEVEL\n            field which is used to group the area codes by province.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16889e1_d16890e1_d16891e1\">To sort using the normal string sort order, use the\n            following ProcScript:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"eds1665702557855__pre_dgm_tjx_tcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">sort/e AREACODES</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16892e1_d16893e1_d16894e1\">In this case, <code class=\"ph codeph\">1.10</code> sorts before\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">1.2</code>:</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eds1665702557855__fig_d16895e1_d16896e1_d16897e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 7. </span>Default Sort for Field LEVEL</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Grid with columns Level, City/Region, and Area Code, using the default sort order on LEVEL, which puts 1.10 before 1.2.\" class=\"image\" id=\"eds1665702557855__image_fgm_tjx_tcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sortareacodeslevel_string.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16901e1_d16902e1_d16903e1\">To sort on the basis of the hierarchical level, use\n            the following ProcScript instruction:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"eds1665702557855__pre_ggm_tjx_tcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">sort/e AREACODES, \"LEVEL: level\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16904e1_d16905e1_d16906e1\">Now <code class=\"ph codeph\">1.2</code> sorts before\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">1.10</code>\n</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eds1665702557855__fig_d16907e1_d16908e1_d16909e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 8. </span>Field Sorted by Level</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Grid with columns Level, City/Region, and Area Code, sorted by LEVEL.\" class=\"image\" id=\"eds1665702557855__image_hgm_tjx_tcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sortareacodeslevel_level.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eds1665702557855__section_ok1_njx_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d259011e314\">Example: Sorting by Multiple Elements </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16916e1_d16917e1_d16918e1\">Uniface enables you to sort by more than one element\n            or field, which is also known as multi-level sorting. For example, a single area code\n            may be assigned to multiple cities or regions.</p>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eds1665702557855__fig_d16919e1_d16920e1_d16921e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 9. </span>Multiple Regions with the Same Area Code</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Grid with columns Level, City/Region, and Area Code. It shows the regions Yukon, Northwest Territories, and Nunavut have the same area code.\" class=\"image\" id=\"eds1665702557855__image_wpq_pjx_tcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sortareacodesmultilevel1.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eds1665702557855__p_d16925e1_d16926e1_d16927e1\">To sort by AREACODE and then by REGION:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"eds1665702557855__pre_xpq_pjx_tcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">sort/e \"AREACODES.TEL\", \"AREACODE: a <span class=\"ph gold\">;</span>REGION: a\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"eds1665702557855__fig_d16928e1_d16929e1_d16930e1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 10. </span>Data Sorted by AREACODE, then REGION</figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Grid with columns Level, Region, and Area Code, sorted by AREACODE, then REGION\" class=\"image\" id=\"eds1665702557855__image_ypq_pjx_tcc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/sortareacodesmultilevel2.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527089\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527089\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Using Sort Options Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Using Sort Options The following examples demonstrate how you can use the sort options to control sorting behavior. The specific examples use the sort statement, but the sort options can also be used with lists. For more information, see Sorting Lists and Sublists . Example: Sort Order You can explicitly set the search order by specifying the ascending or descending search option (or their abbreviations). For example, given a set of occurrences of entity TEL_CODES: Figure 1. Unsorted List of Countries Use the following command to sort in descending order by country: sort/e TELCODES, COUNTRY: descending Copy Figure 2. Countries Sorted in Descending Order By default, Uniface sorts data using a binary sort order. However, if the locale is specified, it can apply locale-based rules for sorting data using $nlssortorder . For more information, see Sorting Based on Locale . Example: Removing Items with Duplicate Values It is possible to remove duplicate items from a list using the unique sort option. For example, an entity TELCODES has fields representing the international calling codes for countries (ICODE and COUNTRY). Both Canada and the United States have the international calling code of 1 : Figure 3. Duplicate Field Values The following ProcScript instruction sorts the list by calling code and removes occurrences with a duplicate value: sort \"TELCODES.TEL\", \"ICODE: u\" Copy Only the first occurrence of the duplicate value is included in the result. Figure 4. Unique Field Values Example: Sorting Using Data Type When sorting occurrences, Uniface uses the data type of the specified sort field. Thus, a numeric field is sorted in numerical order, a Date field is sorted according to its internal data format, and will therefore sort correctly. ( For more information, see Internal Data Format .) If you specify a data type or data type format, for example Numeric or $number , it overrides the field's default data type. When sorting lists, all data is treated as string data by default. Specifying another data type is particularly useful when the ElementToSortBy has data type String but contains numbers, because the sort is by character, which results in 100 sorting before 19. For example, the TELCODES entity has its field PK defined as a string. The following ProcScript instruction sorts occurrences by the PK field: sort/e \"TELCODE\", \"PK: a\" Copy This results in PK=11 sorting before PK=2 . Figure 5. String Field With Numbers Sorted as String To sort the field as a numeric data type, use the following ProcScript instruction: sort/e \"TELCODE\", \"PK: a numeric\" Copy Figure 6. String Field With Numbers Sorted as Numeric Example: Sorting by Hierarchical Level You can also specify a hierarchical sort if the ElementToSortBy contains numbers that represent a hierarchy, such as n.n.n , where each period represents another level in the hierarchy. For example, the following list of telephone are codes for Canada has a LEVEL field which is used to group the area codes by province. To sort using the normal string sort order, use the following ProcScript: sort/e AREACODES Copy In this case, 1.10 sorts before 1.2 : Figure 7. Default Sort for Field LEVEL To sort on the basis of the hierarchical level, use the following ProcScript instruction: sort/e AREACODES, \"LEVEL: level\" Copy Now 1.2 sorts before 1.10 Figure 8. Field Sorted by Level Example: Sorting by Multiple Elements Uniface enables you to sort by more than one element or field, which is also known as multi-level sorting. For example, a single area code may be assigned to multiple cities or regions. Figure 9. Multiple Regions with the Same Area Code To sort by AREACODE and then by REGION: sort/e \"AREACODES.TEL\", \"AREACODE: a ; REGION: a\" Copy Figure 10. Data Sorted by AREACODE, then REGION Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}